#. <section class="sutta" id="dn7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "dn7:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Long Discourses 7"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn7:0.2"
msgid "Jāliyasutta"
msgstr "With Jāliya"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.159"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "dn7:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "dn7:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgctxt "dn7:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena dve pabbajitā—"
msgstr "Now at that time two renunciates—"

msgctxt "dn7:1.4"
msgid ""
"muṇḍiyo ca paribbājako jāliyo ca dārupattikantevāsī yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"the wanderer Muṇḍiya and Jāliya the pupil of Dārupattika—came to the Buddha "
"and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "dn7:1.5"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"ṭhitā kho te dve pabbajitā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they stood to one side "
"and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn7:1.6"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ nu kho, āvuso gotama, taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ, udāhu aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ "
"sarīran”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Gotama, are the soul and the body the same thing, or they are "
"different things?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "dn7:1.7"
msgid "“Tena hāvuso, suṇātha sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, reverends, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "dn7:1.8"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te dve pabbajitā bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "dn7:1.9"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs2"></a>
msgctxt "dn7:2.1"
msgid "“idhāvuso, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ, sammāsambuddho … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“Take the case when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully "
"awakened Buddha …"

msgctxt "dn7:2.2"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is accomplished in ethics. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.160"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "dn7:2.3"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn7:2.4"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "They enter and remain in the first absorption …"

msgctxt "dn7:2.5"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ nu kho tassetaṃ "
"vacanāya:"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant knows and sees like this, would it be appropriate to say of "
"them:"

msgctxt "dn7:2.6"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti."
msgstr ""
"‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are "
"different things’?”"

msgctxt "dn7:2.7"
msgid ""
"Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ tassetaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr "“It would, reverend.”"

msgctxt "dn7:2.8"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn7:2.9"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ jānāmi evaṃ passāmi."
msgstr "“But reverends, I know and see like this."

msgctxt "dn7:2.10"
msgid "Atha ca panāhaṃ na vadāmi:"
msgstr "Nevertheless, I do not say:"

msgctxt "dn7:2.11"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are "
"different things’. …"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs3"></a>
msgctxt "dn7:3.1"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr "They enter and remain in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "dn7:3.2"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "dn7:3.3"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "dn7:3.4"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ nu kho tassetaṃ "
"vacanāya:"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant knows and sees like this, would it be appropriate to say of "
"them:"

msgctxt "dn7:3.5"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti?"
msgstr ""
"‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are "
"different things’?”"

msgctxt "dn7:3.6"
msgid ""
"Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati kallaṃ, tassetaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr "“It would, reverend.”"

msgctxt "dn7:3.7"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn7:3.8"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ jānāmi evaṃ passāmi."
msgstr "“But reverends, I know and see like this."

msgctxt "dn7:3.9"
msgid "Atha ca panāhaṃ na vadāmi:"
msgstr "Nevertheless, I do not say:"

msgctxt "dn7:3.10"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are "
"different things’. …"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs4"></a>
msgctxt "dn7:4.1"
msgid "ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti …"
msgstr "They extend and project the mind toward knowledge and vision …"

msgctxt "dn7:4.2"
msgid ""
"yo kho, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ nu kho tassetaṃ "
"vacanāya:"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant knows and sees like this, would it be appropriate to say of "
"them:"

msgctxt "dn7:4.3"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti."
msgstr ""
"‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are "
"different things’?”"

msgctxt "dn7:4.4"
msgid ""
"Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati kallaṃ tassetaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr "“It would, reverend.”"

msgctxt "dn7:4.5"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn7:4.6"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ jānāmi evaṃ passāmi."
msgstr "“But reverends, I know and see like this."

msgctxt "dn7:4.7"
msgid "Atha ca panāhaṃ na vadāmi:"
msgstr "Nevertheless, I do not say:"

msgctxt "dn7:4.8"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā … pe …."
msgstr ""
"‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are "
"different things’. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "dn7:5.1"
msgid "Nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’"

msgctxt "dn7:5.2"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, kallaṃ nu kho tassetaṃ "
"vacanāya:"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant knows and sees like this, would it be appropriate to say of "
"them:"

msgctxt "dn7:5.3"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti?"
msgstr ""
"‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are "
"different things’?”"

msgctxt "dn7:5.4"
msgid ""
"Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ jānāti evaṃ passati, na kallaṃ tassetaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr "“It would not, reverend.”"

msgctxt "dn7:5.5"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn7:5.6"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ jānāmi evaṃ passāmi."
msgstr "“But reverends, I know and see like this."

msgctxt "dn7:5.7"
msgid "Atha ca panāhaṃ na vadāmi:"
msgstr "Nevertheless, I do not say:"

msgctxt "dn7:5.8"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are "
"different things’.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "dn7:5.9"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn7:5.10"
msgid "Attamanā te dve pabbajitā bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the two renunciates were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn7:5.11"
msgid "Jāliyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
